    "narrative": "The LawDog lineup for April 29 is anchored by **Lawrence Butler**, who leads our rotation with an elite 73.43 efficiency score. Despite the lower batting order spot, his massive 10% park factor boost and 15% SP skill advantage against Wacha make him our premier offensive catalyst. Close behind is **Daulton Varsho** (70.72), who benefits from a favorable matchup against Bello. With an elite platoon edge and solid park factors, both **Lawrence Butler** and **Daulton Varsho** are positioned to drive our scoring, particularly in HR and RBI production. **Jonathan Aranda** (67.67) and **Cal Raleigh** (67.47) also provide strong value; **Cal Raleigh** is particularly enticing due to his elevated batting order position, while **Jonathan Aranda** capitalizes on a strong 12% dynamic platoon edge against Williams.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involved **Geraldo Perdomo**, whose 58.54 score keeps him in the utility slot despite a marginal projection. He narrowly edged out **Gleyber Torres**, who landed below our strict 40.0 efficiency floor at 37.95 due to an unfavorable matchup against Ritchie. The aggressive choice to bench **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez** reflects the high difficulty of the Ritchie start, prioritizing long-term cap preservation over immediate, high-risk volume. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a staple in our lineup (65.79); while his SP skill adjustment is negative, the \"slow delivery\" factor against Rasmussen keeps his steal potential high, a crucial metric given our specific organizational emphasis on the scarcity of SB.\n\nWe are actively monitoring the status of the outfield, as the postponement of **Taylor Ward** removes a significant middle-order bat from today\u2019s calculus. While we are comfortable with our current configuration, owners should note that **Masyn Winn** is our highest risk-adjusted start (41.17). His score is propped up slightly by wind conditions, but the matchup against Chandler is tough. Provided no late-breaking weather shifts occur, we are confident in the efficiency of the current 7-man core to maximize our 5x5 output while maintaining strict discipline regarding our games-played limits.",
